Omninuera — HR Pre‑Offer Checklist (AI Intern, 3 months, Bengaluru)

1) Confirm engagement model
- ⬜ Decide: On‑payroll (employee) or Off‑payroll (training allowance). Document decision.

2) Gather factual inputs (must have)
- ⬜ Company headcount (total employees on payroll). (Answer required.)
- ⬜ Whether intern is a current student and whether the internship is part of curriculum/apprenticeship. (Obtain proof.)
- ⬜ Whether internship will be part of Apprentices Act (if so, register).

3) Prepare and use the revised offer (use attached redline)
- ⬜ Insert the revised internship classification clause, stipend/tax clause, IP assignment clause, background consent clause, termination clause, governing law clause (Bengaluru).
- ⬜ Keep original draft unchanged; issue the redlined version to candidate as the offer.

4) Documents to collect before first payment
- ⬜ PAN card copy (mandatory).
- ⬜ Bank account details for stipend payment.
- ⬜ Aadhaar or government photo ID.
- ⬜ Proof of Bengaluru residence (utility bill, rental agreement) if location compliance is necessary.
- ⬜ Proof of student status/enrolment or apprenticeship registration (if relying on trainee exemption).
- ⬜ Signed Background Verification Consent.
- ⬜ Signed Confidentiality & IP Assignment (can be integrated into the offer acceptance).
- ⬜ Declaration of other employment and expected annual income (for TDS assessment).

5) Payroll / Compliance steps (depending on on/off‑payroll decision)
- If on‑payroll:
  - ⬜ Register intern in payroll system and compute pay components.
  - ⬜ Withhold TDS under Section 192 (if tax due) and prepare to issue Form 16.
  - ⬜ Assess EPF/ESI applicability; register and commence contributions if required.
  - ⬜ Withhold professional tax per Karnataka rules (if applicable).
  - ⬜ Maintain statutory registers (as required).
- If off‑payroll (training allowance):
  - ⬜ Pay stipend as training allowance from a non‑payroll ledger or specific code; issue stipend receipts.
  - ⬜ Maintain documentation showing training character: learning plan, supervisor assignments, progress reports, final certificate.
  - ⬜ Still collect PAN and tax declaration; withhold TDS if applicable.

6) Background checks and privacy
- ⬜ Engage authorised third‑party verifier (if used).
- ⬜ Ensure signed consent is obtained before checks commence.
- ⬜ Store background check data securely and set retention schedule.

7) IP & confidentiality
- ⬜ Ensure the candidate signs the IP assignment and confidentiality agreement before starting.
- ⬜ If equipment is provided (laptop), record asset issuance and return terms.

8) Communication & onboarding
- ⬜ Provide learning plan and reporting manager details.
- ⬜ Clarify weekly expected hours and flexibility.
- ⬜ Provide expense reimbursement process and pre‑approval requirements.

9) Recordkeeping
- ⬜ Keep copy of signed offer, signed consents, proof of student status, stipend payment records, bank transfer receipts, and final training certificate.
- ⬜ Maintain audit file to evidence training nature (useful in case of regulatory review).

10) If uncertain or company has ≥20 employees
- ⬜ Obtain confirmatory advice from payroll/tax counsel or local EPFO/ESIC office on contribution obligations before issuing the offer.

Contact for queries
- HR Contact: [Name / Email / Phone]
- LegalContact: LegalAdvisor (through LegalOrchestrator)

